      public void setDuration​(org.elasticsearch.common.unit.TimeValue duration)
      Set the forecast duration A period of time that indicates how far into the future to forecast. The default value is 1 day. The forecast starts at the last record that was processed.
      Parameters:
      duration - TimeValue for the duration of the forecast

    • getExpiresIn

      public org.elasticsearch.common.unit.TimeValue getExpiresIn()

    • setExpiresIn

      public void setExpiresIn​(org.elasticsearch.common.unit.TimeValue expiresIn)
      Set the forecast expiration The period of time that forecast results are retained. After a forecast expires, the results are deleted. The default value is 14 days. If set to a value of 0, the forecast is never automatically deleted.
      Parameters:
      expiresIn - TimeValue for the forecast expiration

    • getMaxModelMemory

      public org.elasticsearch.common.unit.ByteSizeValue getMaxModelMemory()

    • setMaxModelMemory

      public ForecastJobRequest setMaxModelMemory​(org.elasticsearch.common.unit.ByteSizeValue maxModelMemory)
      Set the amount of memory allowed to be used by this forecast. If the projected forecast memory usage exceeds this amount, the forecast will spool results to disk to keep within the limits.
      Parameters:
      maxModelMemory - A byte sized value less than 500MB and less than 40% of the associated job's configured memory usage. Defaults to 20MB.
